ys susceptibility for polygenic Alzheimer disease?": "APOE", "The DiGeorge/Shprintzen syndrome is caused by a deletion in which chromosome?": "22", "X-chromosome inactivation": "results in genetically turning off one of the two X chromosomes in female mammals", "The pattern of inheritance shown by glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase (G6PD) deficiency is:": "X-linked recessive.", "Homeobox sequences": "are present in the genome of many animal species", "Which of the following karyotypes is diagnostic of Down syndrome": "46,XX,der(14;21)(q10;q10)pat+21", "Nature is more important for ______ differences, while nurture has greater influence on ______ differences.": "structural and anatomical; psychological and social", "Which of the following would result in Angelman syndrome?": "Paternal UPD 15", "Recombinant alpha-iduronidase is used for the treatment of which disease/syndrome?": "Hurler syndrome", "Research from Moshe Szyf and colleagues has provided significant findings on the epigenetic influences of prenatal maternal stress. This work has been labelled ______.": "social epigenetics", "If both parents are affected with the same autosomal recessive disorder then the probability that each of their children will be affected equals ___.": "1", "The mutational mechanism in \u03b4\u03b2-thalassaemia consists of:": "a deletion.", "Assuming Hardy-Weinberg equilibrium, the genoypte frequency of heterozygotes, if the frequency of the two alleles at the gene being studied are 0.6 and 0.4, will be:": "0.48", "Familial hypercholesterolaemia is caused by mutations in the gene which encodes what?": "Low density lipoprotein receptor", "A cross between two true breeding lines one with dark blue flowers and one with bright white flowers produces F1 offspring that are light blue. When the F1 progeny are selfed a 1:2:1 ratio of dark blue to light blue to white flowers is observed. What genetic phenomenon is consistent with these results?": "incomplete dominance", "The proportion of babies that have an abnormality identifiable at birth is _____.": "1 in 40", "______ explained genetic disorders such as alkaptonuria and albinism.": "Recessive inheritance has", "Which of the following conditions shows anticipation in paternal transmission?": "Huntington disease", "A homeotic mutation is one which": "substitutes one body part for another in development", "Which of the following is not a familial cancer syndrome": "Waardenburg syndrome", "The epigenetic inheritance system has been described as ______ (Mayr and Provine, 1980).": "soft inheritance", "Severe anaemia at birth is a feature of what?": "Alpha-thalassaemia", "If an X-linked recessive disorder is in Hardy-Weinberg equilibrium and the incidence in males equals 1 in 100, then the expected incidence of affected homozygous females would be _______.": "1 in 10 000", "Tay-Sachs disease is caused by deficiency of _________________?": "Hexosaminidase A", "A nonsense mutation involves:": "the creation of a stop codon.", "The polymerase chain reaction or PCR is a technique that": "uses short DNA primers and a thermostable DNA polymerase to replicate specific DNA sequences in vitro.", "The maternal serum level of alpha-fetoprotein (AFP) is lower than average in which situation?": "Down syndrome", "______ has been described as the phenomenon by which one genotype can give rise to a range of different physiological or morphological states in response to different environmental conditions during development (West-Eberhard, 1989).": "Developmental plasticity", "Arabidopsis is advantageous for plant genetic research because:": "it is a small plant with a small genome size which can be raised inexpensively", "The proportion of genes shared by first cousins is on average ___.": "1.0/8", "Which of the following is not a tumour suppressor gene?": "RET", "Which of the following is a feature of X-linked dominant inheritance?": "Transmitted by males only to females", "On average, how many fragments would a restriction