rrier screening?": "Oculocutaneous albinism", "Which of the following disorders does not show X-linked inheritance?": "Tay-Sachs disease", "The most common chromosome abnormality in first trimester spontaneous miscarriages is:": "trisomy.", "Which of the following karyotypes is not compatible with survival to birth?": "45,Y", "Male breast cancer is associated with mutations in ___.": "BRCA2", "Pseudocholinesterase deficiency is associated with increased sensitivity to what?": "Succinylcholine", "The most common cystic fibrosis mutation consists of:": "a deletion.", "The normal human chromosome diploid number is:": "46", "Advantages of using adenoviruses for gene therapy include:": "low risk of insertional mutagenesis.", "Which of the following statements about Hirschsprung disease is incorrect?": "It is more common in girls than in boys.", "Which of the following conditions is caused by a trinucleotide (triplet) repeat expansion?": "Huntington disease", "Which of the following causes female pseudohermaphroditism?": "Congenital adrenal hyperplasia", "Which component of transcribed RNA in eukaryotes is present in the initial transcript but is removed before translation occurs?": "Intron", "Which of the following is not a recognized complication of cystic fibrosis?": "Cancer of the oesophagus", "Which of the following diagnostic techniques is of no value for the diagnosis of neural tube defects?": "Chorion villus sampling (CVS)", "Which of the following conditions is a peroxisomal disorder?": "Zellweger syndrome", "Marked microsatellite instability is a feature of:": "hereditary non-polyposis colon cancer (HNPCC).", "The common mutation in \u03b1-thalassaemia consists of:": "a deletion.", "A baby born with pulmonary hypoplasia secondary to oligohydramnios caused by renal agenesis would be classified as having:": "a sequence.", "The ______ is the set of observable characteristics and is the sum of genetic and environmental effects.": "phenotype", "Which of the following