ome is caused by mutations in the gene which encodes _______.": "Fibrillin", "If an autosomal recessive disorder which shows Hardy-Weinberg equilibrium has an incidence of 1 in 6400 then the frequency of carriers is approximately _______.": "1 in 40", "Tracing of a cell lineage during development means that": "the cells giving rise to and derived from a specific cell are known", "Mutations which occur in body cells which do not go on to form gametes can be classified as:": "somatic mutations", "Assuming that the level of glucose is low, a mutation in the repressor of the lac operon in E. coli, preventing binding of the repressor to the operator, should result in:": "constitutive expression of the lac operon genes", "The \u201csticky ends\u201d generated by restriction enzymes allow": "pieces of DNA from different sources to hybridize to each other and to be joined together", "The presence of an extra digit is referred to as __________.": "polydactyly", "Which of the following statements about heritability are true?": "is a measure of the proportion of variation that is due to genetic causes", "Large triplet repeat expansions can be detected by:": "Southern blotting.", "DNA ligase is": "an enzyme that joins fragments in normal DNA replication", "A gene showing codominance": "has both alleles independently expressed in the heterozygote", "Which of the following conditions does not show multifactorial inheritance?": "Marfan syndrome", "The stage of meiosis in which chromosomes pair and cross over is:": "prophase I"}